==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Osteophone
<hw>Os"te*o*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'oste`on</grk> bone + <grk>fwnh`</grk> voice.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for transmission of auditory vibrations through the bones of
the head, so as to be appreciated as sounds by persons deaf from causes
other than those affecting the nervous apparatus of hearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osteoplast</ent>⟦br⟧
